(16268, 1, '2016-05-18 18:18:33', '2016-05-18 18:18:33', '[vc_row type="grid" background_image="16225" background_color="#f3f3f3"][vc_column][vc_empty_space height="100px"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1>Important notice for Health Care Business Owners in California</h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_separator color="#999999"][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_column_text]The State of California now requires most health care companies to carry liability insurance as well as worker’s compensation! As of today, California’s home health agencies, home care organizations, hospices and RCFEs are all required to have valid worker’s compensation insurance and certain minimum limits of general and professional liability coverage.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Businesses that fail to carry such insurance are having their licenses revoked. In addition, the Department is fining companies $200,000 for failure to carry worker’s compensation and may send the responsible owners to jail for 6 months! The state is also cracking down on companies not carrying the required liability insurance and fining owners huge sums of money after closing them down!</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Worker’s Compensation</strong>\r\n\r\nBliss Marc can help you avoid these massive fines and risks at a huge discount!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blissmarc.com/workers-compensation/">Click here to learn more&gt;</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Liability Insurance\r\n</strong><strong>Home Health Agencies, Home Care Organizations, and Hospice</strong>\r\n\r\nAll HHAs, HCOs, and Hospices in California must now have an employee dishonesty bond, including third-party coverage, with a minimum of ten thousand dollars ($10,000), and general and professional liability insurance policy in the amount of at least one million dollars ($1,000,000) per occurrence and three million dollars ($3,000,000) in the aggregate. We can save you money in meeting your California insurance requirements and help you avoid being fined!\r\n<a href="http://blissmarc.com/professional-general-liability/">Click here to learn more</a>&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>RCFEs</strong>\r\n\r\nAB 1523 mandated that all Residential Care Facilities for the Elderly (RCFEs) in California must carry liability insurance. The state requires you to prove your RCFE has general property damage, bodily injury, and professional (E&amp;amp;O) liability coverage of $1 Million per claim / $3 Million aggregate. This insurance can be so expensive that you have to close your doors, or, the state will fine you out of business for not carrying it. But Bliss Marc is here to help. We can beat the rates offered by other insurers and help you affordably meet state requirements.\r\n<a href="http://blissmarc.com/rcfe-liability-insurance/">Click here for an instant quote&gt;</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>WE CAN SAVE YOU MONEY AND HELP YOU AVOID A STOP ORDER, A FINE, OR HAVING YOUR LICENSE REVOKED!</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blissmarc.com/contact/">Call or email us today! </a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"]\r\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_empty_space height="100px"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'California', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16220-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-18 18:18:33', '2016-05-18 18:18:33', '', 16220, 'http://blissmarc.com/16220-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
