fornia insurance requirements and help you avoid being fined!\r\n<a href="http://blissmarc.com/professional-general-liability/">Click here to learn more</a>&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>RCFEs</strong>\r\n\r\nAB 1523 mandated that all Residential Care Facilities for the Elderly (RCFEs) in California must carry liability insurance. The state requires you to prove your RCFE has general property damage, bodily injury, and professional (E&amp;amp;O) liability coverage of $1 Million per claim / $3 Million aggregate. This insurance can be so expensive that you have to close your doors, or, the state will fine you out of business for not carrying it. But Bliss Marc is here to help. We can beat the rates offered by other insurers and help you affordably meet state requirements.\r\n<a href="http://blissmarc.com/rcfe-liability-insurance/">Click here for an instant quote&gt;</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>WE CAN SAVE YOU MONEY AND HELP YOU AVOID A STOP ORDER, A FINE, OR HAVING YOUR LICENSE REVOKED!</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blissmarc.com/contact-2/">Call or email us today! </a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"]\r\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_empty_space height="100px"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'California', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16220-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-14 19:57:39', '2016-05-14 19:57:39', '', 16220, 'http://blissmarc.com/16220-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(16258, 1, '2016-05-14 20:17:35', '2016-05-14 20:17:35', '[vc_row type="grid" background_image="16103"][vc_column][vc_empty_space height="100px"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1>Bond Insurance</h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_separator color="#969696"][vc_empty_space height="20px"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Home Health Care Agencies are required by law in many states and by Medicaid to be licensed <em><strong>and bonded</strong></em> in order to conduct business. A surety bond establishes legitimacy for an agency and is required in order to prove that they are not engaging in fraudulent activity. Bonds ensure that any money owed to third party companies is paid properly and timely. Bonded HHAs are <em>far less likely to be suspect in the eyes of the community and the government</em>.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Home Health Care Agencies need to follow a few simple steps in order to apply for bonds. Bliss Marc will help you a) determine which surety bond is best for your agency and b) that you receive the best quotation. Other criteria required to apply for a bond:</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Complete application</li>\r\n 	<li>Undergo a credit check</li>\r\n 	<li>Submit financial statements</li>\r\n 	<li>Good financial standing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nContact us today to get started on the easy process to receiving your Medicare/Medicaid Surety Bond. Bliss Marc understands your business, and we worked hard to defeat the CMS Bond, BUT it has become a reality. We can provide you a simple process to valid Medicare/Medicaid Surety Bonds priced well below market rates and with many opportunities for discounts. No one can beat our bond solutions as we work with Treasury-listed companies to get you the best value. In addition, Bliss Marc are HHA, Medicare, and Medicaid experts: we will get you the right Surety Bond and help you submit this correctly to CMS and/or your state.\r\n\r\n<strong>ERISA BOND</strong>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Employee Retirement Income Security Act (ERISA) regulates most types of employee benefit plans. A fidelity bond covers those responsible for managing the benefit plan. These bonds protect the participant and any beneficiaries from unjust fraud from anyone who handles the plan assets. In essence, an <b>ERISA fidelity bond</b> is a type of insurance that protects the plan against losses caused by acts of fraud or dishonesty. Fraud or dishonesty includes without limitation larceny, theft, embezzlement, forgery, misappropriation, wrongful abstraction, wrongful conversion, willful misapplication, and other acts. ERISA Plans are required to hold bonds of no less than 10% of the plan assets. Bliss Marc can help guide your ERISA plan to an affordable, secure bond structure. Unbonded fiduciaries raise major red flags with DOL. We can help you avoid this for a reasonable cost.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>EMPLOYEE DISHONESTY BOND</strong>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">These bonds, also known as "Fidelity Bonds," cover employers from losses as it pertains to dishonest or negligent action of their employees. Employers are reimbursed for employee losses such as theft, fraud and embezzlement of a company’s cash and/or assets. Employers should have Employee Dishonesty Bonds when one or more employees handle cash or company assets. You should be able to trust your employees. But the fact is, according to a national survey, one third of all employees admitted stealing from employers during the previous year. The average time it takes for an employer to catch on to active fraud is typically 18 months and a full third of business bankruptcies are a direct result of employee theft (US Chamber of Commerce &amp; The American Society of Employers). All of this can be avoided by working with Bliss Marc to find the right, affordable Employee Dishonesty Bond for your business.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height="20px"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"]\r\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_empty_space height="50px"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Bond Insurance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16066-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-14 20:17:35', '2016-05-14 20:17:35', '', 16066, 'http://blissmarc.com/16066-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
