ere to learn more&gt;</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Assisted Living, etc.</strong>\r\n\r\nWashington statutes mandate that all licensed assisted living and residential treatment facilities in Washington must carry liability insurance. The state requires you to prove your facility has general property damage, bodily injury, and professional (E&amp;amp;O) liability coverage of $1 Million per claim / $3 Million aggregate. This insurance can be so expensive that you have to close your doors, or, the state will fine you out of business for not carrying it. But Bliss Marc is here to help. We can beat the rates offered by other insurers and help you affordably meet state requirements.\r\n<a href="http://blissmarc.com/rcfe-liability-insurance/">Click here for an instant quote &gt;</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>WE CAN SAVE YOU MONEY AND HELP YOU AVOID A STOP WORK ORDER, A FINE, OR HAVING YOUR </strong><strong>LICENSE REVOKED!</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blissmarc.com/contact/">Call or email us today!</a>\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"]\r\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_empty_space height="100px"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Washington', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16352-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-28 14:17:39', '2016-06-28 14:17:39', '', 16352, 'http://blissmarc.com/16352-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
